@baseUrl = http://localhost:8096

###
### Dashboard API Tests
### Controller: DashboardApiController
### Validation: @NotBlank on id path parameter, @Valid on request body
### Response: Returns DashboardDto JSON on success
### Error format: JSON {"error": "message"} for validation/not found errors
###

### Get dashboard by ID - Success
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/dashboard/test-dashboard-id
Accept: application/json

### Get dashboard by ID - Not Found
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/dashboard/non-existent-id
Accept: application/json

### Get dashboard by ID - Invalid ID (blank) - expects 404 Not Found
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/dashboard/
Accept: application/json

### Create new dashboard - Success
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/dashboard
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "My Dashboard",
  "description": "Test dashboard for development",
  "items": []
}

### Create dashboard - Minimal data (id will be auto-generated)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/dashboard
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "items": []
}

### Update dashboard - Success
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/dashboard/test-dashboard-id
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": "test-dashboard-id",
  "name": "Updated Dashboard",
  "description": "Updated description",
  "items": []
}

### Update dashboard - Not Found
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/dashboard/non-existent-id
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Updated Dashboard",
  "description": "Updated description",
  "items": []
}

### Update dashboard - Invalid JSON (expects 400 Bad Request)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/dashboard/test-id
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Invalid",
  "description": "",
  "items": []
